Not the anon you're responding to, but I have to give you some intense autism. I apologise in advance.
Please don't use imgur for bulk image storage and distribution. Most images are already compressed using lossy compression. Imgur will arbitrarily shift between using lossless and lossy compression based on filesize and image dimensions, which at a gamble adds additional lossy compression to that. The results are generally quite visible and irreversible. You're taking the things you're trying to store and share, and actively destroying them slowly over time.
I greatly appreciate your generosity in helping that anon find the content he was looking for, but all the same I implore you to consider more archival-friendly solutions in the future.
